---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import FAQItem from '../components/FAQItem.astro';
import { u } from '../utils/url';
---

<Layout
  title="FAQ – Frequently Asked Questions"
  description="Answers to common questions about Kiwibins Horowhenua rubbish collection – bin-out times, weight limits, what can't go in, bin care, and delivery times."
  canonicalPath="/faq/"
>

  <Hero
    headline="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subheadline="Everything you need to know about your kiwibin. Can't find your answer? Give us a call."
    compact
  />

  <section class="py-14 bg-white" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="sr-only">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div
        class="space-y-3"
        itemscope
        itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage"
      >

        <FAQItem question="When do I have to put my wheelie bin out?" id="bin-out-time" defaultOpen>
          <p>
            Please have your kiwibin kerbside, <strong>facing the street, by 7am</strong> on your collection day. Our trucks start early and we can't come back if you miss us.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">Check the <a href={u('/when-and-where/')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline font-medium">When &amp; Where page</a> to confirm your collection day.</p>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="How soon can I get my bin?" id="delivery-time">
          <p>We aim to deliver your kiwibin within <strong>3 working days</strong> of your order being confirmed. We'll be in touch to arrange delivery.</p>
          <p class="mt-2">Ready to order? <a href={u('/bins-and-prices/')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline font-medium">See our bins and pricing →</a></p>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="What is the maximum weight I can put in my kiwibin?" id="weight-limits">
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 mt-1">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-4 h-4 bg-kiwi-100 text-kiwi-700 rounded-full text-xs flex items-center justify-center font-bold" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span><strong>120-litre kiwibin:</strong> maximum 15 kg</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-4 h-4 bg-kiwi-100 text-kiwi-700 rounded-full text-xs flex items-center justify-center font-bold" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
              <span><strong>240-litre kiwibin:</strong> maximum 30 kg</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-500">The lid of your bin must be able to shut. If extra bags are placed on top, they will be left to go back in the bin for next week.</p>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="What can't I put in my kiwibin?" id="prohibited-items">
          <p class="mb-3">To keep our team safe and our truck running smoothly, the following items <strong>cannot</strong> go in your kiwibin:</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
            {[
              'Toxic, dangerous or hazardous waste (paint, oil, batteries)',
              'Hot ashes',
              'Liquid waste',
              'Engine/car parts and tyres',
              'Steel, metal, or aluminium sheets or poles',
              'Concrete, earth, bricks, stones, sand, soil, or clay',
              'Large branches or wood pieces',
              'Timber offcuts',
              'Whiteware and defunct appliances',
              'Glass or sharp objects (must be double-wrapped if necessary)',
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                {item}
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">Download our <a href={u('/assets/pdfs/bin-care-sheet.pdf')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline" download>Wheelie Bin TLC guide (PDF)</a> for the full list.</p>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="How do I show my kiwibin some TLC?" id="bin-care">
          <p class="mb-3">A little care goes a long way to keeping your bin in good shape:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {[
              'Wrap or bag your rubbish before putting it in the bin',
              'Keep the bin clean – give it a rinse occasionally',
              'Avoid compacting rubbish tightly inside',
              'Only put in household rubbish and green waste',
              'Don\'t over-fill – the lid must be able to shut',
            ].map((tip) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-kiwi-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                </svg>
                {tip}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
            Download our full <a href={u('/assets/pdfs/bin-care-sheet.pdf')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline" download>Wheelie Bin TLC care sheet (PDF)</a> for more tips.
          </p>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="What payment options are available?" id="payment">
          <p>We offer flexible payment frequencies to suit your budget:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li>Weekly, Fortnightly, Monthly, 3-Monthly, 6-Monthly, or Yearly</li>
            <li>Save <strong>5%</strong> when paying 3-monthly, <strong>10%</strong> at 6-monthly, or <strong>15%</strong> when paying yearly</li>
            <li>Direct debit or internet banking accepted</li>
            <li>44-gallon drum service: cash on the day, or direct debit/internet payment</li>
          </ul>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="Which Levin zone am I in?" id="levin-zones">
          <p>Levin is split into three collection zones (Purple, Orange, and Green) with different days. The easiest way to find your zone is to:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Check the colour sticker on your existing kiwibin lid</li>
            <li>Use the <a href={u('/when-and-where/')} class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline font-medium">When &amp; Where page</a> area selector</li>
            <li>Call us on <a href="tel:063688586" class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline">06 368 8586</a> and we'll look it up for you</li>
          </ul>
        </FAQItem>

        <FAQItem question="Does the drum service work the same way as wheelie bin collection?" id="drum-service">
          <p>
            The 44-gallon drum service runs on a text-booking system. Text <a href="sms:0212033205" class="text-kiwi-600 hover:underline">021 203 3205</a> to book an empty and we'll come out and sort it.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Payment is cash on the day or by direct debit/internet banking. $23 per empty.</p>
        </FAQItem>

      </div>

      <!-- Still got questions -->
      <div class="mt-12 card bg-kiwi-50 border-kiwi-200 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-kiwi-900 text-lg mb-2">Still got questions?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-5">Give us a call or send us a message. We're happy to help.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
          <a href="tel:063688586" class="btn-primary text-sm py-2.5 px-5">
            Call 06 368 8586
          </a>
          <a href={u('/contact-us/')} class="btn-secondary text-sm py-2.5 px-5">
            Send a message
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
